<item>
            <title>[SOLR-1088] newSearcher(String name, boolean readOnly) is broken</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/SOLR-1088</link>
                <project id="12310230" key="SOLR">Solr</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;Noted on the mailing list while investigating something semi-related, the method SolrCore.newSearcher(String name, boolean readOnly) doesn&apos;t work as advertised (the readOnly option is completely ignored)&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;the method isn&apos;t used anywhere in Solr (that i could find) but it might be used by clients ... we should deal with this in some way prior to the 1.4 release (either fix; fix &amp;amp; deprecate; or document problem and deprecate)&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;http://www.nabble.com/Re%3A-Lucene-sync-bottleneck--p22237748.html&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow&quot;&gt;http://www.nabble.com/Re%3A-Lucene-sync-bottleneck--p22237748.html&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;</description>
                <environment></environment>
